    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S1_Title">Welcome to ClickyKeys!</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S1_Body">Let me walk you through a quick tutorial.&#10;Feel free to interact with the app at any time — click Next to continue.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S2_Title">Panels</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S2_Body">These are your display panels — the main feature of ClickyKeys.&#10;Each panel counts presses of its assigned key.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S3_Title">Editing a panel</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S3_Body">Left-click any panel to open the editor and assign a key to it.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S3_Hint">👆 Click the panel to try it</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S4_Title">Description and key</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S4_Body">Type a name in the Description field.&#10;Then click Input and press the key you want to track.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S5_Title">Saving changes</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S5_Body">Confirm your changes with the green ✔ button, or discard them with the red ✖.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S6_Title">Appearance</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S6_Body">Open the Appearance tab to customise colours, grid size, fonts, and more.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S6_Hint">👆 Appearance button</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S7_Title">Applying changes</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S7_Body">Click Save at the bottom of Appearance to save your current layout and override current profile.&#10;Unsaved changes will be discarded after closing Appearance tab.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S8_Title">Creating a new layout</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S8_Body">Click Save As at the bottom of Appearance to save your layout under a new name. Enter a new profile name and click Save.&#10;Saved profiles can be loaded from the Load tab.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S9_Title">Transparent mode</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S9_Body">The Transparent mode button hides the background and toolbar — useful for streaming overlays.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S9_Hint">👆 Transparent mode button</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S10_Title">Stats</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S10_Body">The Stats tab shows how many keys you've pressed in total.&#10;Your data is stored only on your local drive.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S10_Hint">👆 Stats button</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S11_Title">Info</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S11_Body">Visit the Info tab to learn more about the ClickyKeys project or watch this tutorial again.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S11_Hint">👆 Info button</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S12_Title">That's it!</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Tutorial_S12_Body">Enjoy using ClickyKeys! 🎉</sys:String>

</ResourceDictionary>
